ENTERPRISE ERP PLATFORM — HRM & CRM AGENT ONBOARDING (MASTER CONSOLIDATED)

blockquote>**Status:** FINAL / AUTHORITATIVE / ENFORCEABLE blockquote>**Audience:** HRM & CRM Engineers, UI Agents, Backend Agents blockquote>**Rule:** This document is the SINGLE source of truth. blockquote>Any deviation is a governance violation.

PAGE 1 — PURPOSE & GOVERNANCE

01login.png

Purpose

This document consolidates **ALL architectural, governance, UI, and execution rules**

required for HRM and CRM development in the Olivine Enterprise ERP Platform.

Goals:

  • Zero ambiguity for new agents
  • Copy–paste mergeability
  • UI and UX consistency
  • Long-term architectural integrity

This is **not guidance**.

This is a **contract**.

PAGE 2 — ENTERPRISE SHELL & APP ISOLATION

Enterprise Shell

erp-platform/

├── retail/

├── hrm/

├── crm/

├── fms/

└── common/

Rules:

  • Each app is independently developable
  • Apps may live on different machines
  • Final integration is folder-level copy–paste
blockquote>COPY → PASTE → RUN is mandatory.

If this fails, the architecture is INVALID.

PAGE 5 — LICENSING vs COMPANY vs LOCATION

Licensing (Commercial Control Plane)

  • Controls entitlements and limits
  • Enables / disables apps
  • OWNS NO BUSINESS DATA
  • OWNS NO MASTERS

Company (Platform Domain)

  • Legal business entity
  • Lives in common/domain
  • Consumed by ALL apps

Location (Retail Domain)

  • Retail-only operational concept
  • MUST NOT be referenced by HRM or CRM

PAGE 6 — DOMAIN OWNERSHIP (LOCKED)

Platform / common (READ-ONLY CONTRACTS)

  • Company
  • User
  • Permission
  • Role
  • AuthPolicy
  • ItemMaster (base)
  • Supplier (base)
  • UnitOfMeasure

HRM Domain

  • Employee
  • Department
  • Position
  • Operates strictly at Company level

CRM Domain

  • Lead
  • Opportunity
  • Account
  • Operates strictly at Company level

❌ NO Location references allowed.

PAGE 7 — MERGEABILITY CONTRACT

Rules:

  • HRM / CRM must run without Retail present
  • Copy–paste of hrm/ or crm/ must work
  • No refactor after merge

Violation = architecture failure.

PAGE 8 — UI CANON (OLIVINE RULE SET)

02mainscreen.png

Core Principles

  • Enterprise-first
  • Dense, functional UI
  • No decorative design
  • Predictability over creativity

Layout Rules

  • Fixed left sidebar
  • Header for global actions only
  • Content scrolls

Transaction Toolbar (MANDATORY)

  • Fixed position
  • Save / Cancel / Reset
  • Workflow actions
  • Keyboard shortcuts

Lookup Rules

  • ALWAYS right-side panel
  • NEVER inline in form
  • Reusable lookup components only

PAGE 9 — SCREEN TYPES

03cust-listing.png
03cust-entry.png
04po-transction-listing.png
04po-transction-entry.png

Master Screens

  • Form-first
  • Toolbar-driven CRUD
  • No inline tables

Transaction Screens

  • Header context
  • Line grid
  • Summary section
  • Workflow toolbar

Configuration Screens

  • Grouped sections
  • Explicit save/reset
  • No auto-save

PAGE 10 — FORM & VALIDATION RULES

  • Explicit required fields
  • Blur-level soft validation
  • Save-level hard validation
  • Read-only clearly indicated
  • No hidden mandatory fields

PAGE 11 — SIDEBAR & MENU GROUPING

Rules:

  • Sidebar reflects domain ownership
  • HRM & CRM menus operate at Company level
  • NO Retail menus duplicated
  • ONE UI per master (no duplicates)

PAGE 12 — DO / DO NOT (ENFORCEMENT)

DO

  • Follow canon strictly
  • Reuse templates
  • Ask before deviating

DO NOT

  • Rebrand UI
  • Create alternate layouts
  • Duplicate masters
  • Ignore rules for speed

PAGE 13 — QUALITY & AUDIT GATES

Before approval:

  • Canon compliance
  • No Location leakage
  • No Licensing masters
  • Copy–paste merge test passes

PAGE 14 — FINAL LOCK

blockquote>Licensing controls access. blockquote>Company anchors all domains. blockquote>Retail owns Location. blockquote>HRM and CRM remain clean, isolated, and mergeable.

Any violation is a **governance breach**.

PAGE 15 — CRITICAL MODEL REFERENCES

Company Model (MANDATORY SHARED)

blockquote>Since all apps operate at the Legal Entity level, you MUST link your models to the Company.
  • **Canonical Source:** `core.licensing.backend.business_entities.models`
  • **Reference Strategy:** Use Lazy String Reference to avoid circular imports.

    • - ✅ `company = models.ForeignKey('business_entities.Company', ...)`

    - ❌ `from core... import Company` (Avoid)

  • **Constraint:** **READ-ONLY**. You must not modify the Company model.

Reference Definition (Do Not Edit)

class Company(models.Model):

    """

    Company Model - LICENSING METADATA ONLY

    """

    class LegalEntityType(models.TextChoices):

        SOLE_PROPRIETOR = "SOLE_PROP", "Sole Proprietor"

        PARTNERSHIP = "PARTNERSHIP", "Partnership"

        PRIVATE_LIMITED = "PRIVATE_LTD", "Private Limited"

        PUBLIC_LIMITED = "PUBLIC_LTD", "Public Limited"

        LLP = "LLP", "LLP"

        NON_PROFIT = "NONPROFIT", "Non Profit / NGO"

        GOVERNMENT = "GOV", "Government"

        OTHER = "OTHER", "Other"



    class Status(models.TextChoices):

        ACTIVE = "ACTIVE", "Active"

        INACTIVE = "INACTIVE", "Inactive"



    # Core identification fields

    code = models.CharField(max_length=32, unique=True)

    name = models.CharField(max_length=255)

    legal_entity_type = models.CharField(max_length=20, choices=LegalEntityType.choices)

    country = models.CharField(max_length=2)

    default_currency = models.CharField(max_length=3)

    timezone = models.CharField(max_length=64)

    status = models.CharField(max_length=8, choices=Status.choices, default=Status.ACTIVE)



    # Structured address

    address_line1 = models.CharField(max_length=255, blank=True)

    address_line2 = models.CharField(max_length=255, blank=True)

    city = models.CharField(max_length=128, blank=True)

    state = models.CharField(max_length=128, blank=True)

    postal_code = models.CharField(max_length=32, blank=True)

    address_country = models.CharField(max_length=2, blank=True)



    created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)

    updated_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now=True)



    class Meta:

        app_label = "business_entities"

        db_table = "be_company"

        verbose_name = "Company"

        verbose_name_plural = "Companies"

Location Model (STRICTLY FORBIDDEN)

blockquote>Location is a Retail Operations concept.
  • **Rule:** HRM and CRM must **NEVER** import or reference `Location`.
  • **Violation:** Any Reference to `Location` = **Immediate Audit Failure**.
